                <h1>The Ultimate Guide to Hanging Peel and Stick Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>To hang peel and stick wallpaper effectively, start with a clean, dry surface. Measure and cut your wallpaper pieces to fit. Peel back a corner of the backing and align it with your starting point. Slowly peel away the backing while smoothing the wallpaper with a flat edge to eliminate bubbles. For best results, work from top to bottom.</p>
